    thinking: "**Considering the Application\'s Focus**\n\nOkay, I\'m currently focused on defining the scope of Germ\303\241n\'s application, Sitiens. I\'m taking into account his interest in the moral, ethical, biological, anthropological, and historical facets of human-animal relationships. I\'m considering veganism, climate change, and pleasure as interconnected aspects to explore within this unique web app.\n\n\n**Analyzing Ethical Boundaries**\n\nI\'m now delving into leisure, future privation theories, biological limits, and supplementation to refine the ethical scope. Germ\303\241n\'s structured approach is evident, but he\'s feeling swamped with the technical aspects: taxonomy, visualization, representing consensus levels (absolute, gray areas, dilemmas, fallacies), live coding, and more.\n\n\n**Evaluating Ecological Footprint**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing understanding the ecological and ethical footprint of user choices, focusing on specific, measurable metrics. I\'ve ruled out Firebase integration for now; client-side storage is preferable for Germ\303\241n\'s current needs, since he wants to explore the ideas first. I\'m excited about the potential of a \"Thesis Validator\" or \"Argument Analyzer\" using the Gemini API. However, I\'m waiting for a direct request before integrating it, as per instructions.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Client-Side Stability**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the structure of the application. The user wants a client-side SPA, and I\'m focusing on that approach for maximum speed and stability. I\'m investigating the potential use of React, Tailwind, and other modern web technologies. I must determine if server-side components are necessary, but for now, the priority is to solidify the client-side architecture and functionality.\n\n\n"
