    thinking: "**Establishing Ethical Frameworks**\n\nI\'ve successfully created `src/types.ts`. It\'s populated with comprehensive Spanish prose exploring ethics, sentience, bivalves, dehesas, and ethical consensus. The goal is to meet Germ\303\241n\'s requirement for rigorous, academic content, avoiding oversimplification by offering structured information for future consideration.\n\n\n**Analyzing Project Scope**\n\nI\'m now diving into the implications of the single-view constraint. Initially, I was thinking about interactive sub-components and layout principles (desktop-first, mobile-first, no unrequested navigation bars), but the instructions are stricter than I initially interpreted. I need to determine if Germ\303\241n\'s request qualifies as a \"simple, short request\" or a more complex conceptual project, given its intricate nature.\n\n\n**Designing Unified Display**\n\nI\'ve decided on a single, unified dashboard layout with a tabbed sub-view selector for a clean and elegant display. This approach prioritizes a pristine visual layout, avoiding sidebars and ensuring a professional feel. I plan to build it as an interactive, premium single-view hub. Now, my focus is designing `/src/components/NetworkGraph.tsx`, starting with an HTML5 Canvas-based graph component to build a visual connection web.\n\n\n**Developing Interactive Canvas**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in developing the interactive `<NetworkGraph />` component. My plan involves a custom canvas implementation, incorporating physics for dynamic particle links and node interactions, as Germ\303\241n requested a high-tech representation. I\'ll include core features like circular/beautiful node placement, glowing link visualization, and detailed side panel displays upon node selection. I\'ll ensure handling of drag-and-drop, touch events, and dynamic window resizing using `ResizeObserver`, avoiding fixed calculations.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/NetworkGraph.tsx` file. This component implements an elegant, high-performance HTML5 Canvas-based interactive network graph. It connects Germ\303\241n\'s 12 core thematic nodes as interconnected nodes in a force-directed system, uses a `ResizeObserver` on the parent container (as instructed by the framework constraints), supports dragging, clicking to zoom, and renders smooth bezier glowing connection lines. When a node is clicked, it enters focus, displaying its scientific facts and philosophical connections."
