    thinking: "**Concluding the Craft**\n\nI\'ve successfully completed the building and restarting phase. There are no further tools I need to employ. Now, I will craft the concluding summary, ensuring it adheres to the communication guidelines specified for this endeavor.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully built and compiled the **Sitiens** full-stack web application structure. The codebase has been optimized, fully resolved, and verified using both standard TypeScript linting and production bundling.\n\nWe have moved the Gemini API integration entirely to the server-side as recommended for full-stack apps. You can manage or inspect the active API credentials inside the **Settings > Secrets** panel.\n\n### Overview of the Implemented Architecture and Design:\n\n- **Visual Concept & Aesthetic Choices**:\n  - The application is framed by a clean, high-contrast **Slate & Obsidian Theme** (`zinc-950` and `zinc-900`) utilizing generous negative space, crisp typography pairings (Inter, Fira Code, and Serif styles), and a dark ambient upper gradient to guide visual focus.\n  - Interactive transitions and subtle micro-animations (powered by `motion`) reinforce hierarchy during tab and item changes.\n\n- **Interactive Core Modules**:\n  - **El Grafo (Force-Directed Graph)**: An interactive, fluid 2D canvas simulation mapping critical pillars of physical nociception, historical utility, thermal inefficiencies, and moral choice. Users can drag individual nodes to witness physical repulsion forces and trigger detailed scientific deconstructions.\n  - **Tesis & Dilemas**: A structured clinical register representing historic excuses (such as the trophic food chain logic, plant nociception myths, or the bio-sustainable pasture paradox). Each item features exhaustive medical, evolutionary, and ethical refutations.\n  - **El Cuantificador (Impact Calculator)**: An interactive scale tool that quantifies the ecological friction of standard diets, mapping the annual cubic meters of water, carbon dioxide emissions, deforested jungle square meters, and lost cereal grain that feed average dietary choices.\n  - **Sitiens IA deconstrucci\303\263n (Socratic Dialectic)**: Equipped with a lazy-loaded server-side `gemini-3.5-flash` model, this module splits custom user arguments socr\303\241ticamente into implicit unconscious axioms, verifies scientific validity, detects cognitive dissonance, and returns an incisive reflection.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 628575711
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
